</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[189,1399,1444,1787]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
At present, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1918" box="[444,628,1444,1470]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[444,628,1444,1470]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Paraschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes with certainty only three species: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Silvestri, 1897)" baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1897" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coeculum">
<emphasis box="[1135,1276,1444,1470]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. coeculum</emphasis>
(Silvestri, 1897)
</taxonomicName>
, distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[476,543,1479,1505]" name="Spain" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Spain</collectingCountry>
to the Balkans, 
<taxonomicName authority="Arcangeli, 1935" authorityName="Arcangeli" authorityYear="1935" box="[741,1086,1479,1506]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanum">
<emphasis box="[741,886,1479,1505]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. hispanum</emphasis>
Arcangeli, 1935
</taxonomicName>
from southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1272,1342,1479,1505]" name="Spain" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Spain</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Frankenberger, 1940" authorityName="Frankenberger" authorityYear="1940" box="[189,554,1514,1541]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roubali">
<emphasis box="[189,303,1514,1540]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. roubali</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Frankenberger Z." box="[311,554,1514,1541]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="7 - 11" refId="ref25667" refString="Frankenberger Z. 1940. Paraschizidium roubali sp. n. (Isopoda - Oniscoidea). Vestnik ceskoslovenske zoologicke Spolecnosti v Praze 8: 7 - 11." type="journal article" year="1940">Frankenberger, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[626,710,1515,1541]" country="Czech Republic" name="Praha" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Prague</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[722,909,1514,1540]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Frankenberger Z." box="[924,1167,1514,1541]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="7 - 11" refId="ref25667" refString="Frankenberger Z. 1940. Paraschizidium roubali sp. n. (Isopoda - Oniscoidea). Vestnik ceskoslovenske zoologicke Spolecnosti v Praze 8: 7 - 11." type="journal article" year="1940">Frankenberger 1940</bibRefCitation>
), which is probably a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Silvestri" baseAuthorityYear="1897" box="[439,581,1550,1576]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coeculum">
<emphasis box="[439,581,1550,1576]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">P. coeculum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Manicastri C. &amp; Taiti S." box="[646,936,1550,1576]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="125 - 150" refId="ref25978" refString="Manicastri C. &amp; Taiti S. 1994. Gli isopodi terrestri dell'Appennino umbro-marchigiano (Crustacea, Oniscidea). Biogeographia 17: 125 - 150." type="journal article" year="1994">Manicastri &amp; Taiti 1994</bibRefCitation>
). Other species from 
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1276,1550,1576]" name="Greece" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Greece</collectingCountry>
originally included in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1918" box="[466,650,1585,1611]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[466,650,1585,1611]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Paraschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Schmalfuss (1981) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Sfenthourakis S." box="[997,1244,1585,1611]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="199 - 209" refId="ref27484" refString="Sfenthourakis S. 1992. New species of terrestrial isopods (Isopoda, Oniscidea) from Greece. Crustaceana 63: 199 - 209." type="journal article" year="1992">Sfenthourakis (1992</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sfenthourakis S." box="[1261,1321,1585,1612]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref27509" refString="Sfenthourakis S. 1995. New species of terrestrial isopods (Oniscidea) from the central Aegean islands. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde, Serie A 519: 1 - 21." type="journal article" year="1995">1995</bibRefCitation>
) were transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Verhoeff, 1901" authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1901" box="[489,809,1620,1646]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Schizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[489,618,1620,1646]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Schizidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Verhoeff K. W." box="[629,809,1620,1646]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="417 - 421" refId="ref28173" refString="Verhoeff K. W. 1901. Uber palaarktische Isopoden (7. Aufsatz). Zoologischer Anzeiger 24: 403 - 408, 417 - 421. Available from http: // biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 9745364 [accessed 1 Dec. 2015]" type="journal article" year="1901">Verhoeff, 1901</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmalfuss H." box="[861,1090,1620,1646]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="143 - 151" refId="ref27361" refString="Schmalfuss H. 2008. The terrestrial isopod genus Schizidium (Isopoda: Oniscidea): systematics, distribution, morphology. Stuttgarter Beitrage zur Naturkunde A (New Series) 1: 143 - 151." type="journal article" year="2008">Schmalfuss (2008)</bibRefCitation>
. Our specimens certainly belong to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1918" box="[431,615,1655,1681]" class="Malacostraca" family="Armadillidiidae" genus="Paraschizidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,615,1655,1681]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Paraschizidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: they are depigmented and blind, have no schisma at the posterolateral corner of the pereonite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[579,689,1690,1717]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="50.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[191,1400,983,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[185,1432,975,1954]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Fig. 32. Paraschizidium sp. from Algar do Javali, Montejunto, ♀. A. Specimen in lateral view. B. Cephalon in frontal view. C. Cephalon in dorsal view. D. Pleonite 5, telson and uropods. E. Antennula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3805701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3805701/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 32A</figureCitation>
), the cephalon has oblique antennal lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1284,1690,1717]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="50.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[191,1400,983,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[185,1432,975,1954]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Fig. 32. Paraschizidium sp. from Algar do Javali, Montejunto, ♀. A. Specimen in lateral view. B. Cephalon in frontal view. C. Cephalon in dorsal view. D. Pleonite 5, telson and uropods. E. Antennula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3805701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3805701/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
B–C), the telson is short and triangular (
<figureCitation box="[534,640,1726,1752]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="50.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[191,1400,983,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[185,1432,975,1954]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Fig. 32. Paraschizidium sp. from Algar do Javali, Montejunto, ♀. A. Specimen in lateral view. B. Cephalon in frontal view. C. Cephalon in dorsal view. D. Pleonite 5, telson and uropods. E. Antennula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3805701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3805701/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 32D</figureCitation>
) and the antennula has two articles (
<figureCitation box="[1062,1167,1726,1752]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="50.[189,232,1964,1990]" captionTargetBox="[191,1400,983,1943]" captionTargetId="figure@50.[185,1432,975,1954]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Fig. 32. Paraschizidium sp. from Algar do Javali, Montejunto, ♀. A. Specimen in lateral view. B. Cephalon in frontal view. C. Cephalon in dorsal view. D. Pleonite 5, telson and uropods. E. Antennula." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3805701" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3805701/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 32E</figureCitation>
). Unfortunately, the absence of males in our material does not permit the identification of these specimens to species level.
</paragraph>
